    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Fielding H. Yost was born in Fairview, West Virginia on April 30, 1871. After graduating from West Virginia University in 1897, he accepted the position of football coach at Ohio Wesleyan University. He took similar positions at the University of Nebraska (1898), the University of Kansas (1899), and Stanford (1900). In 1901, he came to the University of Michigan serving as head football coach (1901-1923 and 1925-1927) and director of intercollegiate athletics from 1921 to 1941. Yost died August 20, 1946.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351">
      <p>The Fielding H. Yost papers are Yost's personal papers and document his business and civic activities, family and social life, and his athletic career prior to coming to Michigan. There is some material (most notably photographs and scrapbooks) on is tenure at University of Michigan, but the main documentation of his work as football coach and athletic director is found in the records of the University of Michigan Board in Control of Intercollegiate Athletics. The Yost papers have been arranged into the following series: Correspondence of Fielding and Eunice Fite Yost; Writings and Speeches; Miscellaneous and Personal; Scrapbooks and Clippings; Photographs; and Eunice Fite Yost Papers.</p>
    </arrangement>
